HEADWORD: Astay
<hw>A*stay"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>An anchor is said to be <xex>astay</xex>, when, in heaving it, an
acute angle is formed between the cable and the surface of the
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

